# Git Setup & GitHub Integration
This module covers the essential first steps

## 1. Installation on Linux
To install Git on Ubuntu
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git -y
```
![Git installation](https://github.com/rajkumargdev/workshop_pics/blob/e2e505261d3c2f66d917355ea2341c4ae6ec7aa3/fig1.png?raw=true)

## 2. SSH Key Generation
Generate a new SSH key to securely connect to GitHub without typing your password every time:
```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
```
![ssh key gen](https://github.com/rajkumargdev/workshop_pics/blob/e2e505261d3c2f66d917355ea2341c4ae6ec7aa3/sshgen.png?raw=true)

Go to ssh key location (.ssh)
![ssh key location](https://github.com/rajkumargdev/workshop_pics/blob/e2e505261d3c2f66d917355ea2341c4ae6ec7aa3/sshkeylocation.png?raw=true)

Copy pub key
![copy key](https://github.com/rajkumargdev/workshop_pics/blob/e2e505261d3c2f66d917355ea2341c4ae6ec7aa3/copypubkey.png?raw=true)

